WEBVTT

00:06.214 --> 00:07.507
[grunts]

00:19.686 --> 00:21.688
[coughs]

00:22.564 --> 00:25.316
<i>You've worked hard. That's a fact.</i>

00:26.067 --> 00:28.611
<i>Now, it's time to relax</i>

00:28.695 --> 00:32.073
<i>and there's no better place to relax
than right here.</i>

00:32.573 --> 00:35.118
<i>Palm Sunshine is not a home.</i>

00:35.702 --> 00:37.370
<i>It's a paradise.</i>

00:39.414 --> 00:42.000
<i>Start your day with friends by the pool,</i>

00:42.083 --> 00:46.129
<i>then join us at the Sunshine Bistro
for lunch or dinner</i>

00:46.671 --> 00:51.426
<i>and be sure to take a stroll
around the five acres of luscious greenery</i>

00:51.634 --> 00:54.679
<i>before returning
to your easy access bungalow,</i>

00:54.846 --> 00:58.349
<i>designed by famed architect Bijan Zanjan.</i>

00:59.517 --> 01:02.771
<i>Feel like going shopping or to the movies?</i>

01:03.104 --> 01:05.899
<i>Let our Sunshine Shuttle take you there.</i>

01:06.691 --> 01:10.612
<i>But why leave when you see
who's performing at the Casbah Cabaret?</i>

01:11.029 --> 01:15.950
<i>Some of the hottest acts in show business
hit the stage five nights a week.</i>

01:17.368 --> 01:21.081
<i>You've taken care of business,
taken care of your family.</i>

01:22.123 --> 01:25.126
<i>Isn't it time somebody took care...
of you?</i>

01:26.252 --> 01:28.088
<i>♪ You've worked hard ♪</i>

01:28.171 --> 01:30.048
<i>♪ That's a fact ♪</i>

01:30.215 --> 01:34.511
<i>♪ Now, it's time to relax ♪</i>

01:34.594 --> 01:39.849
<i>♪ At Palm Sunshine. ♪</i>

02:12.882 --> 02:14.092
It's The Shins.

02:14.342 --> 02:16.928
Ah, they're terrific. Very emo.

02:17.011 --> 02:18.346
That's really amazing!

02:18.555 --> 02:21.057
You're, like,
only nine years behind in the times.

02:21.850 --> 02:23.610
I've always been hip.
You know that, Jeannie.

02:23.685 --> 02:25.687
You know,
hip people don't say that they're hip.

02:25.770 --> 02:27.814
What am I supposed to listen to?
Lawrence Welk?

02:27.897 --> 02:30.900
You love Lawrence Welk!
You fall asleep to him almost every night.

02:33.403 --> 02:34.779
Did you watch the video?

02:35.697 --> 02:36.697
The video?

02:37.448 --> 02:40.702
Yeah, the DVD. Palm Sunshine?

02:40.827 --> 02:43.204
Oh, you retire from the post office,
not from show business.

02:44.497 --> 02:46.207
- You did.
- No, I didn't!

02:46.291 --> 02:50.336
All my acts died on me, except Max Becker.
At least he's still alive.

02:50.920 --> 02:52.881
Doesn't Max Becker have a new manager?

02:53.756 --> 02:56.885
Yeah, but you never know.
He might drop him.

02:58.011 --> 02:59.888
- Thank you!
- Chicken salad.

03:00.388 --> 03:02.182
- Pastrami.
- We need pickles, the good kind.

03:10.607 --> 03:11.691
What's on your head?

03:13.067 --> 03:14.067
Is that make-up?

03:14.444 --> 03:16.446
Grandpa, you fell again?

03:16.946 --> 03:20.867
I did not fall. I was already down
and please don't use the word "again."

03:22.660 --> 03:24.120
Shecky Greene.

03:24.245 --> 03:27.040
You know how many people my age
know who that is? None!

03:27.123 --> 03:31.544
Bob Hope, Lenny Bruce, Richard Pryor,
all the Jacks and the Jackies.

03:31.628 --> 03:34.047
What, you got Skinny Jack, Fat Jack,
Jack Benny,

03:34.130 --> 03:37.008
Jackie Gleason, Jack Carter, Jackie Mason,
One-Eyed Jack...

03:37.091 --> 03:41.262
You know? You put so much shit in my head
and I kind of love you for it.

03:42.889 --> 03:43.890
Kind of?

03:44.766 --> 03:46.226
Look, maybe...

03:46.935 --> 03:49.437
Well, there was that time with the...

03:50.480 --> 03:53.691
- the stove and then there's...
- What do you want from me, Jeannie?

03:56.778 --> 03:58.404
I don't want you to be alone.

03:59.822 --> 04:02.617
<i>Happy days and a pleasant good night.</i>

04:06.955 --> 04:08.957
<i>Are you a catheter user?</i>

04:09.082 --> 04:11.042
<i>What if your catheter could hide
in plain sight?</i>

04:11.125 --> 04:14.128
<i>I turned 60 this year and I'm not...
Don't.</i>

04:15.630 --> 04:17.257
<i>No need to applaud.</i>

04:17.339 --> 04:19.384
<i>"Gee, he's really in tremendous shape.</i>

04:19.841 --> 04:22.011
<i>I bet he's on a high fibre diet."</i>

04:22.095 --> 04:26.224
<i>I had an oat muffin ten years ago
and I'm still shitting because of it.</i>

04:29.811 --> 04:30.811
<i>I'm a manager.</i>

04:31.062 --> 04:34.941
Mostly, I manage comedians,
like Arty Wise.

04:35.817 --> 04:36.859
Huh.

04:37.151 --> 04:38.194
You a fan?

04:38.569 --> 04:39.988
No, I don't know who that is.

04:40.571 --> 04:45.201
Oh, well, everyone probably older
than you knows Arty Wise.

04:45.827 --> 04:47.370
You'd know him if you saw him.

04:48.246 --> 04:49.998
But you won't see him 'cause he's dead.

04:52.000 --> 04:53.042
Dead and gone.

04:53.459 --> 04:54.585
I'm sorry to hear that.

04:54.669 --> 04:56.713
- I'm Al Hart.
- [cell phone rings]

04:57.422 --> 04:58.422
Hello?

05:00.508 --> 05:02.969
No, I'm free. Perfect timing, yeah!

05:06.347 --> 05:07.348
Hi, sweetheart.

05:08.766 --> 05:09.766
How are you?

05:09.892 --> 05:10.893
Keeping busy?

05:14.772 --> 05:16.941
I could really use your advice, Lois.

05:18.443 --> 05:19.652
I'm a little lost.

05:21.654 --> 05:22.739
How about a sign?

05:23.698 --> 05:24.824
No rain, though.

05:25.700 --> 05:26.909
I walked here.

05:32.623 --> 05:34.417
What am I supposed to do, darling?

05:44.761 --> 05:47.764
<i>♪ You worked hard ♪</i>

05:47.847 --> 05:50.433
<i>♪ That's a fact ♪</i>

05:50.975 --> 05:53.394
<i>♪ Now, it's time to relax... ♪</i>

05:55.813 --> 05:57.899
[woman] I really wish you guys
could stay for dinner.

05:57.982 --> 06:01.027
- Wednesday is Lasagna Night.
- Lasagna Night?

06:01.110 --> 06:02.987
- Yes! Mr Hart...
- Yes?

06:03.071 --> 06:05.114
I think that once you see the campus,

06:05.198 --> 06:07.116
- you'll be very impressed.
- I hope so.

06:07.200 --> 06:10.703
And what better way
to show you the grounds of Palm Sunshine

06:10.787 --> 06:13.289
than to have one of our residents
give you a tour?

06:13.456 --> 06:15.458
[bells ring]

06:15.583 --> 06:16.751
[grunts]

06:16.834 --> 06:18.836
[clears throat, spits]

06:19.379 --> 06:22.256
Did somebody call for a tour guide?

06:23.216 --> 06:25.218
[coughs]

06:27.553 --> 06:29.055
Come on, I don't have all day.

06:32.475 --> 06:33.893
How long you been married?

06:33.976 --> 06:36.604
Oh, no, this is my grandpa.

06:37.397 --> 06:38.689
Yeah, I don't care.

06:40.483 --> 06:42.110
No! Grandpa, come on.

06:42.193 --> 06:44.362
- Just...
- No, let's get out of here.

06:44.445 --> 06:46.864
No, we'll just... A couple of minutes.

06:54.956 --> 06:56.249
Go-go dancers.

06:56.332 --> 06:57.959
Go on, check it out!

07:00.002 --> 07:02.046
- Let's get the hell out of here.
- Okay.

07:02.964 --> 07:04.257
[horns honk]

07:13.474 --> 07:14.809
This is the mess hall.

07:15.768 --> 07:17.186
A potato a day

07:17.270 --> 07:20.565
and soup... made from rocks!

07:20.815 --> 07:21.815
It's horrible!

07:22.442 --> 07:25.862
But never, ever ask for more

07:26.237 --> 07:28.239
or they'll put you in the Box.

07:28.531 --> 07:29.449
The what?

07:29.532 --> 07:32.160
The Box! People die in the Box!

07:32.243 --> 07:33.953
Don't let them put me in the Box...

07:34.036 --> 07:36.164
- I had no intention of...
- You gotta help me!

07:36.247 --> 07:37.247
You gotta help me!

07:37.290 --> 07:40.418
Please, just help me
get a message to my son!

07:40.501 --> 07:41.377
[yells]

07:41.502 --> 07:42.670
Please!

07:43.713 --> 07:45.548
I don't want to do Ed Sullivan.

07:57.185 --> 07:58.269
Buddy?

07:59.145 --> 08:00.145
Buddy Green?

08:00.771 --> 08:02.106
- Al Hart!
- [laughs]

08:02.732 --> 08:04.567
I don't believe this!

08:06.444 --> 08:08.279
- I...
- I got him good!

08:08.362 --> 08:11.282
Got me good.
You know, you son of a bitch, you got old.

08:11.741 --> 08:13.343
- Me?
- That's how I didn't recognize you.

08:13.367 --> 08:16.007
- You look like a mummy.
- How did you know I was even coming here?

08:16.078 --> 08:17.538
I'm the welcoming committee.

08:17.997 --> 08:19.665
I saw your name on the list.

08:20.500 --> 08:22.460
Come on.

08:23.586 --> 08:25.171
What a surprise!

08:25.838 --> 08:28.758
This place is terrific and I mean it,

08:29.217 --> 08:32.845
and I was the most skeptical of all
when I first moved in here.

08:33.638 --> 08:36.640
But my son, he just...

08:37.683 --> 08:39.434
He just talked me into it, you know?

08:41.145 --> 08:44.524
It doesn't bother you,
being around so many old people?

08:44.649 --> 08:45.858
Oh... no...

08:46.526 --> 08:47.985
Never use the O word.

08:48.986 --> 08:49.986
It's very offensive.

08:50.863 --> 08:53.491
The politically correct term is pre-dead.

08:57.703 --> 09:00.373
Buddy Green!
I never thought I'd see you again.

09:01.457 --> 09:02.291
I know.

09:02.375 --> 09:03.876
So, what happened?

09:03.960 --> 09:05.920
Buddy was my first client ever.

09:06.003 --> 09:08.256
He was one of the funniest up-and-comers.

09:08.339 --> 09:09.339
I booked him everywhere.

09:10.174 --> 09:13.302
Then we were doing two weeks
at the Elegante,

09:13.386 --> 09:14.845
opening for Al Martino.

09:15.513 --> 09:17.265
Jerry Vale, and it was the Copa.

09:17.348 --> 09:18.432
No.

09:18.975 --> 09:22.019
I specifically remember
it was Martino at the Elegante.

09:22.103 --> 09:26.148
It was my show and it was Jerry Vale
and it was at the Copa.

09:26.232 --> 09:28.568
You never played the Copa!
I was your manager.

09:28.651 --> 09:31.112
- I should know.
- You are out of your mind!

09:31.195 --> 09:32.613
- No...
- Guys, jeez! Okay.

09:33.197 --> 09:34.615
What happened?

09:35.408 --> 09:37.243
- I get the call.
- From Ed Sullivan?

09:37.326 --> 09:38.828
It's every comic's dream.

09:39.453 --> 09:42.039
It was 1967.

09:42.915 --> 09:44.000
Last time I saw him.

09:45.793 --> 09:48.337
So... you didn't do Ed Sullivan?

09:50.131 --> 09:51.757
What did you end up doing?

09:51.841 --> 09:53.384
I became a podiatrist.

09:54.385 --> 09:56.387
You gave up show business for feet?

09:56.470 --> 09:59.307
Yep. I had the biggest practice
in Beverley Hills...

09:59.473 --> 10:00.600
where nobody walks.

10:03.894 --> 10:06.689
But your grandfather
was a hell of a manager.

10:06.772 --> 10:09.191
- I wasn't that good.
- He was a hell of a lousy manager,

10:09.275 --> 10:11.736
- but he had a way with people.
- I've never liked people.

10:11.819 --> 10:14.256
- He never liked people, but he liked me.
- I never liked you.

10:14.280 --> 10:16.200
He never liked me, per se,
but he liked children.

10:16.282 --> 10:18.659
- Not your children.
- Well, my children were terrible.

10:18.743 --> 10:19.619
My son was a moron.

10:19.702 --> 10:21.287
Can't even remember his own name!

10:22.830 --> 10:23.998
This is his bit!

10:25.291 --> 10:27.084
A guy who would keep
on changing his opinion.

10:27.168 --> 10:28.586
I called it <i>The Agent.</i>

10:30.379 --> 10:31.839
Al Hart!

10:32.590 --> 10:34.091
It's a hell of a surprise.

10:35.384 --> 10:36.927
So, what do you think?

10:41.891 --> 10:43.017
How are the chicks?

10:44.518 --> 10:45.895
Old and horny.

11:30.106 --> 11:31.107
So, what do you think?

11:31.190 --> 11:32.274
Not bad.

11:32.566 --> 11:35.027
Best part of it is,
you don't gotta tip anybody.

11:35.820 --> 11:37.540
Come on,
we're gonna go get some good seats.

11:37.738 --> 11:39.532
[men singing, piano playing]

12:01.220 --> 12:02.221
They're twins.

12:03.264 --> 12:04.264
Ah.

12:11.230 --> 12:12.230
I gotta sit.

12:12.815 --> 12:14.817
[sighs]

12:18.863 --> 12:20.865
You know, I used to think that...

12:21.657 --> 12:24.744
that running a marathon was... tiring.

12:25.578 --> 12:27.496
Now, it's standing up for ten minutes.

12:28.080 --> 12:30.708
- [laughs]
- Buddy, you coming?

12:31.667 --> 12:34.628
Uhh... Yeah, I'll be there in a minute.

12:34.795 --> 12:37.006
Okay? All right, I'll be there.

12:38.591 --> 12:40.968
- Who's that?
- Nobody.

12:41.051 --> 12:42.219
Buddy...

12:42.636 --> 12:44.263
Your girlfriend?
You have a girlfriend?

12:44.638 --> 12:47.433
Well... the cocktail lounge is still open.

12:47.933 --> 12:49.935
Go get yourself a drink and...

12:50.644 --> 12:52.396
and then I'll meet you in the morning,
okay?

12:54.106 --> 12:56.567
Does this ever happen to you,
that when you stand up,

12:56.984 --> 12:59.487
you have to pretend
to be looking at something

12:59.653 --> 13:02.048
- before you get your balance back?
- I don't have all night!

13:02.072 --> 13:03.407
That's your girlfriend, isn't it?

13:03.491 --> 13:04.491
No!

13:05.034 --> 13:06.034
No.

13:06.744 --> 13:07.744
- Buddy?
- It's a friend.

13:07.787 --> 13:09.455
I think she's waiting.

13:10.456 --> 13:11.290
Your mom.

13:11.373 --> 13:13.459
- Yeah.
- Now is the time, Buddy.

13:14.293 --> 13:17.087
- [clears throat]
- You know, the nice thing about this place

13:17.171 --> 13:18.891
is that you don't have
to eat anyone's shit.

13:41.987 --> 13:45.407
Did you hear the one
about the guy who goes to the doctor,

13:45.491 --> 13:47.785
he says, "Doctor, I pee non-stop.

13:47.868 --> 13:50.162
I can't help it, I just keep peeing.
What shall I do?"

13:50.746 --> 13:54.959
The doctor says, "First thing you have
to do is get off my rug."

13:57.253 --> 13:58.253
Okay.

13:58.295 --> 14:00.297
By the way, I got a new shipment.

14:00.381 --> 14:02.258
- Oh, yeah?
- Yeah, from Canada.

14:02.550 --> 14:04.969
- All right.
- A place called Viagra Falls.

14:05.594 --> 14:07.429
Are you telling me you can still...

14:07.513 --> 14:08.597
Like <i>this.</i>

14:09.682 --> 14:11.684
Well, sometimes it's like this.

14:11.851 --> 14:14.895
But Cialis or Viagra, sometimes both...

14:15.479 --> 14:18.399
Doc Ron here, he's my pusher.

14:18.482 --> 14:21.277
If you ever need a hard-on,
this is my card.

14:24.071 --> 14:26.073
[men laugh]

14:27.199 --> 14:29.118
Thank you. Thank you so much, Ron.

14:29.201 --> 14:32.079
Get about a 10-, 15-minute semi.

14:32.162 --> 14:33.789
I'm okay with a semi.

14:34.081 --> 14:35.249
Can you still come?

14:35.457 --> 14:36.876
- Can you still...
- Yes.

14:36.959 --> 14:38.669
Excuse me - orgasm. Yeah?

14:38.836 --> 14:40.754
If you count... dust.

14:42.882 --> 14:43.716
That's terrible!

14:43.799 --> 14:46.343
The last time that my wife got frisky,

14:46.969 --> 14:52.349
we were in bed and she starts
stroking my chest and my stomach

14:52.433 --> 14:55.728
and she slid her hand lower under my ass

14:56.103 --> 14:58.105
and, all of a sudden, she stops

14:58.480 --> 15:00.482
and I'm like, "Why are you stopping?"

15:00.816 --> 15:03.569
And she says, "I found the remote."

15:15.831 --> 15:17.207
You guys hear about Katz?

15:17.791 --> 15:19.752
- Murray Katz?
- Stroke.

15:20.794 --> 15:22.922
Yeah, they ran him down
to Cedars this morning.

15:23.005 --> 15:25.883
- How is he?
- I'm gonna guess... not good.

15:26.342 --> 15:28.552
- And Darlene Lipshaw.
- The tango dancer?

15:29.053 --> 15:30.512
She's a good dancer.

15:30.721 --> 15:31.764
Well, she <i>was.</i>

15:32.014 --> 15:33.933
Fell in the shower, broke her hip.

15:34.642 --> 15:35.559
Anything else?

15:35.643 --> 15:37.811
- And her nose.
- [groans]

15:38.145 --> 15:41.273
Well, I want to thank you
for bringing us the good news.

15:49.949 --> 15:51.867
That was Johnny Sunshine.

16:52.386 --> 16:54.638
Not good.

16:54.972 --> 16:58.600
[Sunshine] Hear about Saul Fischer?
He won $5 at canasta,

16:58.976 --> 17:01.228
went to bed, woke up dead.

17:01.478 --> 17:03.188
Marty Freeman had a knee replacement.

17:03.272 --> 17:06.108
And then they found a tumor on his spine.

17:07.233 --> 17:08.233
That it?

17:08.359 --> 17:09.819
That's not enough for you?

18:04.458 --> 18:08.087
You know, I don’t think I ever knew
that you play the piano.

18:13.592 --> 18:15.219
I'm not there yet, Buddy.

18:24.561 --> 18:27.564
It's... a new season.

18:28.857 --> 18:29.858
Embrace it.

18:38.283 --> 18:42.121
George Burns. He was 100 years old.
He never retired.

18:43.163 --> 18:45.833
Rickles. He couldn’t walk,
but he was still killing ’em.

18:46.750 --> 18:48.127
I'd rather go down working.

18:48.627 --> 18:50.629
[chuckles]

18:51.713 --> 18:52.881
You're not working.

18:59.805 --> 19:03.225
Do you have any idea how hot
old comedians are right now?

19:03.559 --> 19:04.559
What?

19:05.727 --> 19:07.521
There’s a lot of love for the old-timers.

19:11.400 --> 19:13.569
- Are you smoking grass?
- Mmhmm.

19:14.778 --> 19:17.364
- I have a card.
- Since when do you smoke pot?

19:19.366 --> 19:22.536
Since 1965, when The Beatles started.

19:23.412 --> 19:24.955
A pot-smoking podiatrist.

19:29.168 --> 19:30.836
- Want some?
- Not my thing.

19:31.712 --> 19:32.880
You never tried it, did you?

19:36.341 --> 19:38.135
Of course I've tried it!

19:39.386 --> 19:41.226
- It's just not my thing.
- You never tried it.

19:41.263 --> 19:42.639
- I tried it.
- You never tried it.

19:43.932 --> 19:47.394
Oh, God,
you're the most tragically unhip person.

19:47.978 --> 19:50.814
- Like you're hip!
- I am. I am pretty hip.

19:51.148 --> 19:53.150
Hip people do not say they're hip.

19:53.817 --> 19:56.617
And just because I don't act
like a jazz musician doesn't mean I'm not.

19:57.154 --> 19:58.280
Jazz musician?

19:58.906 --> 20:00.532
That's your frame of reference?

20:01.867 --> 20:05.412
That is the most unhip statement
I have ever heard.

20:07.748 --> 20:12.169
Look... can we just talk about this,
just hypothetically?

20:13.462 --> 20:14.755
Talk about what?

20:17.257 --> 20:19.635
Are you telling me you don't miss it?

20:20.677 --> 20:22.179
You could have been big.

20:22.888 --> 20:23.888
I am big.

20:24.306 --> 20:25.849
It's the jokes that got small.

20:27.100 --> 20:28.352
You see? That's funny.

20:29.061 --> 20:32.481
I'm a funny guy, you know?
I used to crack up my patients.

20:33.065 --> 20:36.360
- You had a gift.
- I was just another comic.

20:36.526 --> 20:37.778
I barely had an act.

20:38.028 --> 20:41.365
You... had a personality and you still do.

20:41.448 --> 20:43.659
And, by the way, you're in great shape.

20:44.993 --> 20:48.580
I retired, Al, 50 years ago!

20:48.664 --> 20:50.916
What a great comeback story!

20:50.999 --> 20:54.086
Yeah, from bunions to Broadway!

20:55.045 --> 20:58.840
See, you just can't help but be funny.

20:58.924 --> 21:00.425
I'm a funny guy, okay!

21:00.509 --> 21:04.263
Why not let me get you a few gigs?
Just a few, test the waters.

21:05.222 --> 21:08.392
Because I'm not a comedian, Al.
I'm not!

