Where'd you get this?

44:33.712 --> 44:35.798
I got it from a jazz musician.

44:36.840 --> 44:38.133
Yeah, right!

44:39.968 --> 44:40.968
Thanks.

44:41.220 --> 44:42.429
- Thanks, man.
- Wait a minute.

44:43.389 --> 44:44.389
It's Jeannie.

44:44.640 --> 44:45.640
Your granddaughter.

44:47.768 --> 44:49.770
- What do I do?
- Answer it.

44:51.188 --> 44:52.314
Isn't it a little late?

44:52.398 --> 44:54.483
It's true. That's true. It's very late.

44:54.566 --> 44:57.027
- It's too late to be calling.
- What if it's an emergency?

44:57.111 --> 44:59.738
You're the only emergency possible
and you're alive.

44:59.822 --> 45:01.824
Yep. She can leave a message.

45:02.908 --> 45:05.661
Well, I got a good feeling about Kansas.

45:08.288 --> 45:11.291
Hey, Buddy... I never asked you.

45:13.627 --> 45:14.753
Why did you quit?

45:17.548 --> 45:18.548
Well...

45:19.550 --> 45:20.968
I had a house in the Hills.

45:21.927 --> 45:25.097
I had a swimming pool.
I had a brand-new Jaguar every two years.

45:25.389 --> 45:27.808
I had a wife, who gave me a son,

45:28.392 --> 45:30.185
who gave me three grandchildren.

45:31.019 --> 45:33.856
So, what the fuck did I quit?

46:40.839 --> 46:45.594
<i>"There were only three things standing
between me and Yasgur's Farm that summer.</i>

46:45.677 --> 46:48.806
<i>Two of those hurdles
were not having a car or money.</i>

46:49.389 --> 46:53.310
<i>That wouldn’t stop me
from seeing Janis Joplin at Woodstock.</i>

46:53.393 --> 46:57.272
<i>It was the third obstacle
that was the most difficult.</i>

46:58.190 --> 46:59.483
<i>I was 12.</i>

47:01.151 --> 47:03.529
So, this girl from Overland Park

47:03.612 --> 47:05.823
did what any typical seventh grader
would do.

47:05.906 --> 47:07.282
She tried to hitchhike.

47:07.366 --> 47:11.119
My thumb was out no more than five minutes
before the car pulled up,

47:11.203 --> 47:15.123
which was a 1965 Buick Special.

47:15.207 --> 47:20.170
Coincidentally, the same car
that my father drove,

47:20.254 --> 47:24.633
which wasn't really a coincidence
because it was my father.

47:26.760 --> 47:28.428
I never made it to Woodstock

47:28.512 --> 47:32.474
and I spent those last days of summer
locked in my bedroom,

47:32.891 --> 47:37.145
dreaming of Janis,
who would be dead the following year."

47:38.981 --> 47:40.983
Well, that's the end of the chapter.

47:42.985 --> 47:44.152
Thank you.

47:52.411 --> 47:54.413
Oh, thank you!

48:00.544 --> 48:03.672
Oh, that's so sweet! Thank you.

48:19.479 --> 48:21.023
- Hi.
- Hi.

48:21.106 --> 48:23.150
- MInd if I...
- Please.

48:29.990 --> 48:31.074
I liked your reading.

48:31.158 --> 48:35.287
Oh, thanks. It's a work in progress,
like my life.

48:36.622 --> 48:39.291
I'm Al, by the way.
Al Hart from Los Angeles.

48:39.625 --> 48:41.919
- Doris Lovejoy from...
- Overland Park?

48:42.002 --> 48:43.211
- Yeah!
- Lovejoy...

48:43.295 --> 48:45.297
Lovejoy - is that your stage name?

48:46.006 --> 48:47.758
No. I'm an eighth Pawnee.

48:47.841 --> 48:49.801
- Oh, the Pawnee Lovejoys.
- Yeah!

48:51.136 --> 48:55.015
So, Al Hart from Los Angeles,
what brings you to Kansas City?

48:55.557 --> 48:56.808
I'm on tour.

48:57.643 --> 48:59.853
I knew you were a rock star.

49:00.437 --> 49:02.147
More like Elvis's grandfather.

49:08.195 --> 49:11.031
Say, I'm not usually this forward.

49:12.032 --> 49:14.618
Doris, would you like to have dinner
with me tomorrow?

49:15.577 --> 49:18.038
I don't know, Al. That is just so forward.

49:18.747 --> 49:19.747
You're right.

49:20.290 --> 49:22.376
How about... just soup?

49:27.631 --> 49:28.966
So, do you want my number?

49:29.466 --> 49:31.718
<i>You can have more time
to practice your putting</i>

49:31.802 --> 49:35.305
<i>with the Potty Putter,
the amazing new toilet time golf game</i>

49:35.389 --> 49:38.183
<i>that lets you practice your putting...
on the potty!</i>

49:38.350 --> 49:40.852
<i>Your Potty Putter
comes with its own putting green,</i>

49:40.978 --> 49:44.398
<i>made of the same professional carpet
found at miniature golf courses.</i>

49:44.481 --> 49:48.193
<i>Now, practice your putting every time
you take care of your other business.</i>

49:48.318 --> 49:51.655
<i>Just aim and shoot the ball into the cup.</i>

49:51.863 --> 49:56.576
<i>Just think of all that extra practice,
all only 19.99.</i>

49:56.660 --> 49:59.705
<i>Let your imagination soar
with a Potty Putter.</i>

50:00.539 --> 50:01.832
<i>Don't touch that dial!</i>

50:02.374 --> 50:06.003
<i>Coming up next, the champagne sounds
of The Lawrence Welk Show.</i>

50:06.128 --> 50:09.297
<i>And now, here's your host, Lawrence Welk.</i>

50:11.258 --> 50:13.135
[Doris] Arty Wise?

50:13.218 --> 50:17.097
I adore him!
I used to watch him on Ed Sullivan.

50:17.305 --> 50:19.683
I even went to Vegas to see him once.

50:20.600 --> 50:23.895
Those are my racist family relics.

50:24.187 --> 50:26.398
I painted my family heirlooms.

50:27.232 --> 50:29.484
So, what was he like?

50:30.193 --> 50:31.193
Arty?

50:32.195 --> 50:33.195
He was a mensch.

50:34.698 --> 50:36.033
Stayed with me to the end.

50:44.041 --> 50:46.585
<i>You've reached Al Hart
at Al Hart Management.</i>

50:46.668 --> 50:49.880
<i>Please leave a message at the beep
and we'll get right back to you.</i>

50:55.302 --> 50:58.513
So, what about you?
What were you doing back in the day?

50:58.722 --> 51:03.351
I was probably booking Pat Henry
for Sinatra at the Fontainebleu.

51:03.477 --> 51:04.311
Wow!

51:04.394 --> 51:05.812
You are so hip.

51:07.147 --> 51:09.274
To be honest, I never even smoked pot.

51:09.357 --> 51:10.776
How is that even possible?

51:11.443 --> 51:13.153
I don't like to lose control.

51:14.029 --> 51:16.239
All right, take a hit. There you go.
Oh, wow!

51:16.323 --> 51:18.283
That's it, okay. Hold it in.

51:18.366 --> 51:19.366
[blows]

51:20.535 --> 51:22.370
That was a good hit!

51:22.454 --> 51:24.289
I might as well suck on a muffler.

51:24.664 --> 51:26.958
One more like that
and you'll be good to go.

51:28.210 --> 51:29.252
Here you go.

51:29.753 --> 51:30.837
That's good. Wonderful...

51:32.047 --> 51:34.966
Oh, my God.
I know someone who's gonna love you.

51:36.468 --> 51:38.887
[Doris] I was an art teacher
before I retired.

51:39.221 --> 51:41.932
I used to paint, but now I do these.

51:43.975 --> 51:45.018
[Al] They're magnificent.

51:45.852 --> 51:46.852
Thank you.

51:47.437 --> 51:48.438
No, really.

51:48.939 --> 51:52.067
These are like... Rodin meets Larry Flynt.

51:52.234 --> 51:54.236
[Doris laughs]

51:54.444 --> 51:57.864
I just think it's wonderful
that you guys are doing this.

51:58.156 --> 52:01.076
It must be so exciting
to be back on the road again.

52:02.619 --> 52:06.373
But why did he quit
right before Ed Sullivan?

52:06.748 --> 52:09.042
You would think
he'd want to go out with a bang.

52:10.585 --> 52:11.837
That's a good question.

52:12.295 --> 52:13.295
I don't know.

52:13.755 --> 52:16.299
See what happens when you lose control?

52:17.300 --> 52:19.970
Hey, where are you?

52:20.220 --> 52:21.471
We're supposed to have dinner.

52:21.763 --> 52:22.848
<i>Listen, Buddy,</i>

52:22.931 --> 52:25.308
you mind eating on your own tonight?

52:26.852 --> 52:28.562
Why? What's going on?

52:28.728 --> 52:31.189
<i>It's a long story.</i>

52:31.773 --> 52:33.024
I kind of met someone.

52:33.733 --> 52:34.943
It's crazy!

52:35.026 --> 52:36.111
Hold on.

52:36.236 --> 52:38.238
[woman moaning]

52:39.698 --> 52:40.532
She came.

52:40.615 --> 52:41.950
I'll explain later.

52:42.784 --> 52:45.744
Maybe you can just order from room service
or something. What do you think?

52:45.787 --> 52:49.541
Sure. I'll have them send up a filet
and a crack pipe.

53:14.941 --> 53:18.820
- I'm feeling a little strange, Doris.
- Yeah.

53:20.530 --> 53:21.907
How y'all doing tonight?

53:28.205 --> 53:29.915
[Al] Ah, I'm stuffed.

53:33.043 --> 53:34.961
I love barbecue.

53:35.837 --> 53:37.339
Look at the stars.

53:38.465 --> 53:40.383
Oh, wow!

53:40.675 --> 53:42.219
- What are you doing?
- Oh.

53:43.220 --> 53:45.805
Sometimes in special moments,

53:46.139 --> 53:50.060
I just like to feel the ground.
You should try it.

53:52.187 --> 53:54.564
I never take my shoes off on a first date.

53:55.065 --> 53:56.608
Is this a date?

53:57.484 --> 53:58.485
I don't know.

53:59.569 --> 54:00.737
- Well...
- Is it?

54:00.820 --> 54:03.990
Whatever it is,
it's a pretty special moment.

54:04.699 --> 54:05.784
Don't you think?

54:09.621 --> 54:10.621
Yeah.

54:38.858 --> 54:39.859
That's very nice.

54:56.126 --> 54:56.960
Where am I?

54:57.127 --> 54:58.712
[audience laughs]

54:59.004 --> 55:00.255
Oh, you find that funny?

55:00.714 --> 55:03.800
An old man is lost
and you find that funny?

55:08.096 --> 55:09.222
I discovered him.

55:11.474 --> 55:12.474
Twice.

55:46.760 --> 55:48.762
[Al and Buddy singing]

56:00.732 --> 56:01.732
Okay!

56:22.170 --> 56:24.923
So, what's your plan?

56:25.840 --> 56:27.342
Or are you winging it?

56:27.842 --> 56:28.842
What do you mean?

56:29.427 --> 56:30.762
I mean the girl.

56:31.846 --> 56:32.889
What are you doing?

56:33.765 --> 56:34.765
I don't know.

56:35.725 --> 56:38.436
In all my years,
I've never picked up a girl on the road.

56:38.520 --> 56:40.980
Is she gonna go all the way
to New York with us?

56:41.606 --> 56:42.690
Would you mind if she did?

56:42.774 --> 56:45.026
I don't mind. It's your life.

56:45.110 --> 56:46.110
You see?

56:46.861 --> 56:47.861
You do mind.

56:47.904 --> 56:50.784
There are just certain things
I might have wanted to talk to you about...

56:50.865 --> 56:51.950
What certain things?

56:52.117 --> 56:54.702
Stuff to... talk about.

56:55.286 --> 56:56.287
So, we talk.

56:58.498 --> 56:59.958
Forget it. To hell with me!

57:00.250 --> 57:05.338
Okay, Slim Jims, Cheetos,
pork rinds, cookies!

57:06.673 --> 57:07.673
Hello.

57:08.174 --> 57:09.174
Hi!

57:11.261 --> 57:12.261
Hi!

57:32.282 --> 57:33.825
That's the Palmer House.

57:33.908 --> 57:35.493
I booked you in the Empire Room.

57:35.577 --> 57:37.871
- Remember you were opening for Al Hirt?
- Bobby Hackett.

57:37.954 --> 57:39.247
Bullshit!

57:42.709 --> 57:44.127
Mister Kelly's was right there.

57:44.210 --> 57:46.129
You played on a bill
with Barbra Streisand.

57:46.212 --> 57:47.755
She was probably 19 years old.

57:47.839 --> 57:49.090
I tried to bang her.

57:49.591 --> 57:52.886
Back there, that was the Gate of Horn.
You opened for Peter, Paul and Mary there.

57:52.969 --> 57:53.970
The Kingston Trio.

57:54.053 --> 57:57.056
[Al] All those great clubs - gone.

57:57.515 --> 57:59.184
Where the hell do people go now?

58:31.257 --> 58:33.009
- What are you doing?
- I don't know.

58:33.510 --> 58:35.220
Why aren't you in there with her?

58:36.095 --> 58:36.971
I don't know.

58:37.055 --> 58:39.933
- Isn't that the point?
- We never discussed it.

58:40.016 --> 58:42.018
I'm out of practice,
I don't know what I'm doing.

58:42.101 --> 58:44.771
Isn't it obvious that she wants you

58:44.854 --> 58:46.934
- to spend the night with her?
- You don't know that.

58:46.981 --> 58:49.150
Well, why the hell else would she be here?

58:49.234 --> 58:52.070
- I don't want to be presumptious, okay?
- Oh, God!

58:52.153 --> 58:53.738
You are so nuts!

58:53.821 --> 58:56.157
Hey, guys,
you want to keep it down out here?

58:56.241 --> 58:58.535
- What's going on?
- Don't worry, get back in the room.

58:58.618 --> 59:01.704
You think you're hot shit
'cause you're in <i>Jerry Springer!</i>

59:01.788 --> 59:03.623
- Loser!
- What if she says no?

59:04.666 --> 59:05.917
I can't take the rejection.

59:06.000 --> 59:08.253
Then you can spend the night
in here with me.

59:08.336 --> 59:09.379
You ask her.

59:09.462 --> 59:11.714
Just ask her where I'm sleeping,
that's all.

59:12.215 --> 59:13.841
Don't... Hey, no.

59:13.967 --> 59:16.386
I'm sorry, I don't want to know.

59:17.136 --> 59:18.763
Look, Al...

59:19.264 --> 59:24.394
she's a free love hippie spirit
who went to Woodstock.

59:24.727 --> 59:27.021
If you don't go in there, I will.

59:31.776 --> 59:32.819
I gotta take this.

59:35.405 --> 59:37.323
Vic! How are you?

59:37.907 --> 59:39.325
I've been waiting for your call.

59:39.951 --> 59:41.077
[laughs]

59:41.327 --> 59:42.745
Yeah. So, what's the latest?

59:59.637 --> 01:00:00.763
[Doris] I'm so sorry.

01:00:02.056 --> 01:00:03.057
[Al] Who am I kidding?

01:00:03.266 --> 01:00:06.269
You can't just get somebody
on The Tonight Show.

01:00:07.478 --> 01:00:10.773
Well,
look at all that you've accomplished.

01:00:10.857 --> 01:00:13.943
I would say you've been a great success.

01:00:16.279 --> 01:00:18.740
I think it's wonderful
that you're doing what you love,

01:00:18.823 --> 01:00:23.369
but what about
when you can't do it anymore?

01:00:28.458 --> 01:00:31.127
I will never play canasta!

01:00:31.794 --> 01:00:35.214
I will not take the short bus
to the mall ever again!

01:00:37.717 --> 01:00:40.094
All I know how to do is work.

01:00:41.596 --> 01:00:44.223
I don't know who I am without it.

01:00:49.604 --> 01:00:53.483
You know what I do when I have
a really hard decision to make?

01:00:54.442 --> 01:00:55.442
Mushrooms.

01:00:55.902 --> 01:00:56.986
Shrooms?

01:00:57.654 --> 01:01:00.823
Jesus Christ! I'm falling for a pusher.

01:01:00.948 --> 01:01:02.825
It's a beautiful night, Al,

01:01:02.909 --> 01:01:05.203
and only good things happen
when we let go.

01:01:07.705 --> 01:01:09.957
Uh... Okay.

01:01:38.861 --> 01:01:42.115
[Buddy] I am thinking about a song.

01:01:43.199 --> 01:01:44.199
What?

01:01:45.034 --> 01:01:47.662
I'm thinking about
bringing a song into the act.

01:01:47.745 --> 01:01:50.665
I think it will be a great thing
for The Tonight Show.

01:01:51.624 --> 01:01:52.624
I don't like it.

01:01:52.667 --> 01:01:55.336
- Why not?
- I don't like when comedians sing.

01:01:56.087 --> 01:01:57.171
I hate musicals.

01:01:57.255 --> 01:02:00.425
When somebody just breaks out into song
for no damn reason...

01:02:00.508 --> 01:02:02.635
[Al sings a note]

01:02:02.802 --> 01:02:04.178
That makes me sad.

01:02:04.595 --> 01:02:05.680
I love musicals.

01:02:06.889 --> 01:02:08.224
How are you feeling, Buddy?

01:02:08.307 --> 01:02:10.476
Like a chaperone on prom night.

01:02:15.648 --> 01:02:17.775
Oh, my gosh, look at you guys!

01:02:18.359 --> 01:02:20.111
Wow, what an entrance!

01:02:20.194 --> 01:02:21.320
Hey, Jimbo!

01:02:21.404 --> 01:02:23.656
Al Hart. How are you?

01:02:23.740 --> 01:02:25.867
Never better, man.
I want you to meet somebody.

01:02:27.076 --> 01:02:28.076
Buddy Green.

01:02:30.037 --> 01:02:32.623
- Wow, what an honor!
- Oh, thank you.

01:02:32.707 --> 01:02:35.209
I heard you took a few years off,
like your entire career?

01:02:35.293 --> 01:02:37.044
[laughs] Yeah, a few.

01:02:37.128 --> 01:02:39.255
You look fantastic, Jimbo.
Did you lose weight?

01:02:39.338 --> 01:02:41.424
- I put on 75 pounds.
- Oh, that's what I mean.

01:02:41.507 --> 01:02:44.260
You look good for a fat guy.
Your clothes are very stylish, though.

01:02:44.343 --> 01:02:46.679
- I bought these at Goodwill.
- Stylish in 1985.

01:02:46.763 --> 01:02:47.847
How's your beautiful wife?

01:02:47.930 --> 01:02:49.098
She left me two years ago.

01:02:49.182 --> 01:02:50.057
Ah, good riddance.

01:02:50.141 --> 01:02:51.517
- Never liked her.
- Hey!

01:02:51.601 --> 01:02:53.019
Are you stealing my bit?

01:02:53.102 --> 01:02:55.563
Wait a minute. <i>The Agents </i> is your bit?
I thought it was Al's.

01:02:55.646 --> 01:02:57.857
Al wouldn't know funny if it blew him.

01:02:57.940 --> 01:02:59.025
I think he's hilarious.

01:02:59.275 --> 01:03:01.486
For a manager, but <i>as </i> a manager...

01:03:02.361 --> 01:03:03.362
He booked you here.

01:03:03.446 --> 01:03:04.739
He <i>drove </i> us here.

01:03:04.822 --> 01:03:06.741
- He's a terrible driver.
- He drove from LA!

01:03:06.824 --> 01:03:07.867
Like a pilot.

01:03:09.368 --> 01:03:11.871
- All right.
- Jimbo, I want you to meet Doris.

01:03:11.954 --> 01:03:12.954
Doris, Jimbo.

01:03:13.414 --> 01:03:14.414
I'm the mascot!

01:03:14.957 --> 01:03:18.669
Look at you. You're beautiful!
You're a two knuckler.

01:03:20.087 --> 01:03:21.087
What's a two knuckler?

01:03:22.173 --> 01:03:23.173
[all laugh]

01:03:23.549 --> 01:03:25.760
All right, here,
let me show you your dressing room.

01:03:26.052 --> 01:03:28.452
- Come on. We'll be back out soon.
- Yeah, we'll be right in.

01:03:29.013 --> 01:03:30.598
I'm starting to feel a little tingly.

01:03:32.225 --> 01:03:34.644
God, you look good!
That's a beautiful dress.

01:03:37.021 --> 01:03:38.314
I don't know, I feel...

01:03:39.232 --> 01:03:41.943
Look at the colors, even at night!

01:03:43.986 --> 01:03:45.279
It's good.

01:03:45.488 --> 01:03:48.241
I feel footloose and fancy free.

01:03:50.451 --> 01:03:51.451
Grandpa!

01:03:57.208 --> 01:03:58.626
How strong is this shit?

01:03:59.293 --> 01:04:01.087
I don't think you're hallucinating yet.

01:04:01.170 --> 01:04:02.088
- Hey!
- Jeannie!

01:04:02.171 --> 01:04:03.047
Hi!

01:04:03.172 --> 01:04:04.257
What are you doing here?

01:04:05.591 --> 01:04:08.177
- This is Charlie Green. It's Buddy's son.
- Hi.

01:04:10.596 --> 01:04:11.596
Is this real?

01:04:12.056 --> 01:04:13.641
- This is Charlie Green?
- Yeah.

01:04:13.724 --> 01:04:14.724
This is real?

01:04:16.644 --> 01:04:20.022
I remember you
when you were just a small girl.

01:04:20.857 --> 01:04:23.276
I'm kidding you, Charlie.
Your dad talks about you a lot.

01:04:23.359 --> 01:04:24.527
Is he okay?

01:04:24.610 --> 01:04:26.028
He's in top form.

01:04:26.112 --> 01:04:28.781
He just went in if you want to,
you know...

01:04:30.157 --> 01:04:31.343
- Okay, I'm gonna go in.
- Okay.

01:04:31.367 --> 01:04:33.077
- Excuse me, my dad is inside.
- Okay.

01:04:33.619 --> 01:04:35.830
You've grown into a fine young man,
Charlie.

01:04:38.124 --> 01:04:39.124
Okay. All right.

01:04:39.917 --> 01:04:40.917
A little uptight, huh?

01:04:41.752 --> 01:04:43.921
He's upset. You never called.

01:04:44.005 --> 01:04:46.090
- I didn't call?
- You know you didn't call.

01:04:46.173 --> 01:04:48.134
- I could have sworn we just talked.
- Grandpa!

01:04:48.217 --> 01:04:50.636
I've heard so many lovely things
about you.

01:04:50.720 --> 01:04:52.388
Oh, thank you.

01:04:53.431 --> 01:04:56.058
- I'm sorry, who are you?
- I'm Doris.

01:04:56.142 --> 01:04:57.602
I met Doris in Kansas.

01:04:58.728 --> 01:04:59.728
Not bad, huh?

01:05:00.479 --> 01:05:02.106
Grandpa's still got game.

01:05:02.523 --> 01:05:03.523
Grandpa...

01:05:04.734 --> 01:05:05.734
Can we talk for a sec?

01:05:05.776 --> 01:05:08.863
Sure, you two talk.
I'm gonna go pet the horse.

01:05:09.322 --> 01:05:10.322
Okay.

01:05:10.865 --> 01:05:12.950
His name is Lincoln, as in Abraham.

01:05:13.034 --> 01:05:14.034
No relation.

01:05:15.328 --> 01:05:17.121
It's really good to see you, kid.

01:05:19.081 --> 01:05:20.708
It's good to see you, Dad.

01:05:22.209 --> 01:05:23.669
But what the hell are you doing?

01:05:24.962 --> 01:05:26.130
I'm on tour.

01:05:27.381 --> 01:05:28.966
Since when does my father,

01:05:29.050 --> 01:05:33.721
Dr Edward Green, podiatrist, go on tour?

01:05:34.013 --> 01:05:36.682
You know, nobody ever asked their parents:

01:05:36.807 --> 01:05:39.685
"What did you do
before you were a parent?"

01:05:41.228 --> 01:05:42.730
This is what I did, Charlie.

01:05:43.981 --> 01:05:45.775
I do not understand.

01:05:46.442 --> 01:05:48.069
I was a comic.

01:05:48.653 --> 01:05:51.948
And I could have been maybe big,
maybe not.

01:05:52.323 --> 01:05:56.077
But I didn't stick around long enough
to find out.

01:05:56.160 --> 01:05:58.621
What the fuck are you talking about?

01:05:58.704 --> 01:06:00.998
Are you losing your mind, too?

01:06:01.082 --> 01:06:02.291
I had a cousin, Murray.

01:06:03.918 --> 01:06:08.923
He left his wife and kids and he moved
in with a man named Little Leo.

01:06:09.757 --> 01:06:14.220
Nobody ever asked Murray, "What did you do
before you were a parent?"

01:06:15.846 --> 01:06:17.139
Are you gay, too, Dad?

01:06:18.849 --> 01:06:19.934
No.

01:06:20.893 --> 01:06:22.687
I'm a closeted comedian.

01:06:23.270 --> 01:06:25.398
[Al] That life isn't for me, sweetheart.

01:06:26.023 --> 01:06:27.149
I felt like an inmate.

01:06:27.233 --> 01:06:29.026
So, you drag Buddy into this?

01:06:29.110 --> 01:06:31.195
I didn't drag him anywhere. He came.

01:06:31.278 --> 01:06:32.697
This was his idea.

01:06:33.614 --> 01:06:37.076
Maybe I put the idea in his head,
but it was his decision.

01:06:37.159 --> 01:06:39.078
He shouldn’t be exerting himself.

01:06:39.161 --> 01:06:42.206
Exerting? The guy was humping every night
back at the home!

01:06:42.289 --> 01:06:43.916
Lucky bastard!

01:06:44.250 --> 01:06:46.419
Okay. Grandpa, this is dangerous!

01:06:46.585 --> 01:06:50.256
How is it dangerous?
I mean, he’s in better shape than me.

01:06:51.674 --> 01:06:53.259
You don't know, do you?

01:06:55.136 --> 01:06:57.388
Why are you so upset? Why?

01:06:57.638 --> 01:07:00.182
Really?
None of this makes any sense to you?

01:07:00.266 --> 01:07:01.350
Okay, hey!

01:07:01.767 --> 01:07:04.353
You were missing. Vanished.

01:07:04.937 --> 01:07:08.482
And now I find you living some secret life
as Rodney Dangerfield,

01:07:08.566 --> 01:07:11.944
and I'm just supposed to be thrilled
that you suddenly found yourself at 80?

01:07:12.653 --> 01:07:13.653
Yes.

01:07:14.447 --> 01:07:17.033
Charlie, I know what I’m doing

01:07:17.658 --> 01:07:19.076
I'm a grown man.

01:07:21.579 --> 01:07:22.955
You're also a sick man.

01:07:23.831 --> 01:07:27.376
Why do you even bring that up?
What does that have to do with anything?

01:07:27.710 --> 01:07:28.836
I feel fine.

01:07:32.423 --> 01:07:33.758
Oh, my God...

01:07:35.509 --> 01:07:37.094
It's pancreatic.

01:07:37.219 --> 01:07:38.929
Oh, Jesus!

01:07:39.847 --> 01:07:43.100
That's... the worst kind. I...

01:07:43.517 --> 01:07:45.728
Charlie thinks
that this trip could kill him.

01:07:46.979 --> 01:07:49.065
I don’t know
how to process this right now.

01:07:49.690 --> 01:07:51.484
Grandpa, are you all right?

01:07:52.526 --> 01:07:53.526
Here. Are you Okay?

01:07:54.236 --> 01:07:55.738
It's just the shrooms.

01:07:56.572 --> 01:07:57.572
How bad is he?

01:07:58.240 --> 01:07:59.283
It's terminal.

01:08:00.493 --> 01:08:01.827
What do you mean, "shrooms"?

01:08:09.293 --> 01:08:13.839
When I was a kid, my friends always used
to want to eat dinner at our house.

01:08:16.509 --> 01:08:19.929
I couldn’t understand it
because Mom wasn’t that great a cook.

01:08:22.598 --> 01:08:23.598
But almost every day,

01:08:23.640 --> 01:08:26.102
someone would ask, “Hey, Charlie,
can I come over for dinner?”

01:08:27.353 --> 01:08:29.438
For a second, I thought I was popular.

01:08:31.148 --> 01:08:32.483
You cracked those kids up.

01:08:33.067 --> 01:08:35.528
You were always
the funniest dad in the world.

01:08:36.529 --> 01:08:37.988
You didn't give up a career.

01:08:38.072 --> 01:08:41.200
You just... found a different audience.

01:08:42.451 --> 01:08:45.162
I want my kids to have that experience
while they can.

01:08:45.246 --> 01:08:47.038
They deserve to laugh like that.

01:08:47.997 --> 01:08:49.750
They haven't heard them all yet.

01:08:58.551 --> 01:08:59.551
Hey...

01:09:02.680 --> 01:09:04.682
Oh, Jesus, come on!

01:09:05.683 --> 01:09:07.475
Don't be so dramatic.

01:09:07.560 --> 01:09:09.228
What am I supposed to do?

01:09:12.398 --> 01:09:15.442
Charlie, I've had a great life.

01:09:16.402 --> 01:09:19.529
I didn't live it exactly the way
I thought I would,

01:09:20.113 --> 01:09:23.826
but at least let me die the way I want.

01:09:28.622 --> 01:09:30.957
I should have known.
All that pot he smokes...

01:09:31.375 --> 01:09:32.917
He calls it his medicine.

01:09:34.545 --> 01:09:37.214
Al, he’s all settled.
I’m gonna get you to the table.

01:09:37.881 --> 01:09:38.881
Mascot?

01:09:40.050 --> 01:09:42.011
How's everybody doing?

01:09:42.845 --> 01:09:46.724
He's making a comeback, actually,
after 50 years.

01:09:46.807 --> 01:09:49.560
50. That's 5-0, folks.

01:09:49.810 --> 01:09:52.813
I am serious as a heart attack.
I hope he doesn't have one.

01:09:54.899 --> 01:09:57.318
Ladies and gentlemen,
welcome to the stage

01:09:57.401 --> 01:09:59.028
Buddy Green!

01:10:10.956 --> 01:10:11.956
I love you.

01:10:13.834 --> 01:10:14.960
