01:16:24.746 --> 01:16:26.873
<i>Love, Doris."</i>

01:16:32.462 --> 01:16:33.505
Ah.

01:16:33.797 --> 01:16:35.799
Where did you disappear to last night?

01:16:36.341 --> 01:16:40.178
The best show I ever gave
in my whole life.

01:16:42.389 --> 01:16:45.475
Where did you find it?
I thought I lost it.

01:16:45.559 --> 01:16:47.561
And wait a minute...

01:16:47.811 --> 01:16:49.521
have you seen this?

01:16:50.147 --> 01:16:52.232
Second page of the entertainment section.

01:16:52.316 --> 01:16:54.901
Fallon's people will love this.

01:16:55.319 --> 01:16:58.363
If we hit the road now,
we can make Youngstown by dinner.

01:16:58.447 --> 01:17:01.325
- We can make New York by lunch...
- It's not happening.

01:17:02.367 --> 01:17:03.367
What?

01:17:04.411 --> 01:17:06.580
Vic didn't come through. I'm sorry.

01:17:08.373 --> 01:17:11.460
Look, we did it.
We played all the way to Chicago.

01:17:11.627 --> 01:17:13.545
Let's go back and celebrate.

01:17:14.129 --> 01:17:15.631
What the fuck is this?

01:17:15.714 --> 01:17:19.926
Do you think that I give a shit
about The Tonight Show?

01:17:21.011 --> 01:17:22.888
That was your idea, anyway!

01:17:24.222 --> 01:17:25.766
I'm going to New York!

01:17:25.849 --> 01:17:26.933
It's finished, Buddy.

01:17:28.477 --> 01:17:32.314
It's time to... you know, retire.

01:17:38.737 --> 01:17:43.742
You drag me through the dregs
of third-rate nightclubs

01:17:43.825 --> 01:17:45.661
so I can shit my guts out,

01:17:45.744 --> 01:17:49.414
almost get lynched in Lubbock
with that kooky broad

01:17:49.498 --> 01:17:54.961
and now you're telling me...
that <i>I've </i> got to quit?

01:17:55.837 --> 01:17:59.007
- Maybe that is why Max Becker fired you.
- That's bullshit.

01:17:59.091 --> 01:18:02.886
Maybe that is why
Max Becker is doing the Colbert show

01:18:02.969 --> 01:18:06.556
and you are trying to drag me
back to that fucking home.

01:18:06.640 --> 01:18:08.016
That's bullshit and you know it!

01:18:08.642 --> 01:18:11.395
Becker's playing Colbert. Well, fuck him.
And fuck you.

01:18:11.978 --> 01:18:13.146
Fuck <i>me?</i>

01:18:13.480 --> 01:18:15.107
You're the one who's quitting.

01:18:15.190 --> 01:18:17.776
Oh, really?
You want to talk about quitting?

01:18:17.859 --> 01:18:19.319
You fucked me over, Buddy.

01:18:19.403 --> 01:18:22.239
- Oh, here we go.
- You almost killed my career.

01:18:22.322 --> 01:18:24.449
You let me holding my dick,
just like Arty.

01:18:24.533 --> 01:18:27.411
- I should have anticipated this.
- Just like Becker.

01:18:27.494 --> 01:18:29.496
- You all quit on me, Buddy.
- [Buddy mumbles]

01:18:29.579 --> 01:18:32.082
My whole life, I never quit on one soul.

01:18:32.666 --> 01:18:33.917
Until now.

01:18:38.547 --> 01:18:39.965
[Al sighs]

01:18:42.217 --> 01:18:43.677
I know you're sick, Buddy.

01:18:44.886 --> 01:18:46.054
Jeannie told me, yeah.

01:18:48.223 --> 01:18:49.766
Motherfucker...

01:18:51.768 --> 01:18:53.103
Why didn't you tell me?

01:18:54.479 --> 01:18:56.690
I was gonna tell you after Kansas.

01:18:58.066 --> 01:19:00.068
But that's when
you brought the girl along.

01:19:00.527 --> 01:19:02.112
Christ, sucking...

01:19:03.780 --> 01:19:07.159
terminal goddamn pancreatic bullshit.

01:19:07.409 --> 01:19:08.409
I...

01:19:11.329 --> 01:19:16.835
I could have... two more months
or maybe a year.

01:19:18.044 --> 01:19:20.172
Fucking doctors can't make up their minds.

01:19:20.589 --> 01:19:25.677
It's like the guy whose doctor tells him,
"You've got six months to live."

01:19:26.678 --> 01:19:30.849
And the guy says, "I can't pay the bill."

01:19:31.725 --> 01:19:35.729
And the doctor says,
"Okay, I'll give you another six months."

01:19:38.523 --> 01:19:41.193
I don't regret the choices I've made, Al.

01:19:42.235 --> 01:19:43.235
But...

01:19:44.863 --> 01:19:46.323
If we quit now...

01:19:47.574 --> 01:19:50.160
that will be the only thing...

01:19:51.328 --> 01:19:55.832
this dying man will truly regret.

01:20:00.295 --> 01:20:02.714
Way to fucking milk that disease!

01:20:11.056 --> 01:20:12.056
Hold it!

01:20:12.516 --> 01:20:13.642
Oh, shit!

01:20:14.100 --> 01:20:15.435
- Shit?
- Shit!

01:20:16.269 --> 01:20:17.896
- Shit.
- We're not stopping you.

01:20:17.979 --> 01:20:18.979
We're going with you.

01:20:19.022 --> 01:20:19.856
No shit?

01:20:19.940 --> 01:20:21.066
- No shit!
- Shotgun!

01:20:22.442 --> 01:20:23.610
<i>♪ I'll show you around ♪</i>

01:20:23.693 --> 01:20:24.736
<i>♪ I love it ♪</i>

01:20:24.820 --> 01:20:27.113
<i>♪ Bet your bottom dollar
You'll lose your blues ♪</i>

01:20:27.197 --> 01:20:28.490
<i>♪ In Chicago ♪</i>

01:20:28.907 --> 01:20:30.200
<i>♪ Chicago ♪</i>

01:20:30.283 --> 01:20:33.745
<i>♪ The town
That Billy Sunday could not shut down... ♪</i>

01:20:33.829 --> 01:20:35.747
- Who's Billy Sunday?
- Some asshole.

01:20:35.831 --> 01:20:38.458
<i>- ♪Boys and girls together ♪</i>
- Yeah.

01:20:38.542 --> 01:20:41.086
<i>♪ Me and Mamie O'Rourke ♪</i>

01:20:41.461 --> 01:20:43.964
<i>♪ We tripped the light fantastic ♪</i>

01:20:44.214 --> 01:20:48.385
<i>♪ On the sidewalks of New York... ♪</i>

01:21:29.551 --> 01:21:30.551
[Max]It's instant.

01:21:30.969 --> 01:21:33.346
I don't have a coffee maker.
I don't like clutter.

01:21:34.806 --> 01:21:36.516
That's a touching story, Al.

01:21:37.142 --> 01:21:38.560
I really feel for the guy.

01:21:39.227 --> 01:21:40.437
He should have a shot.

01:21:41.021 --> 01:21:43.023
Especially at the Ed Sullivan Theater.

01:21:43.106 --> 01:21:49.029
That would be... poetic and satisfying,
I'm sure.

01:21:52.699 --> 01:21:54.534
But not in my slot!

01:21:58.705 --> 01:22:00.790
You got a lot of years ahead of you, Max.

01:22:01.541 --> 01:22:02.876
Not to mention...

01:22:02.959 --> 01:22:06.504
and I'm not trying to play the guilt card,
but you kind of owe me one.

01:22:07.339 --> 01:22:08.840
I'm sorry, refresh my memory.

01:22:08.924 --> 01:22:10.926
Did you not get your 10%?

01:22:11.134 --> 01:22:14.888
Is there some outstanding balance
I don't know about?

01:22:14.971 --> 01:22:16.598
You know what I'm talking about.

01:22:16.723 --> 01:22:18.725
police [sirens ring]

01:22:18.808 --> 01:22:20.060
- That was...
- Look, Max,

01:22:20.143 --> 01:22:23.271
I didn't come here looking for an apology
or a handout.

01:22:24.022 --> 01:22:29.069
I came to appeal... to you...
as a human being.

01:22:30.362 --> 01:22:32.447
I'm not a human being. I'm a comedian!

01:22:32.739 --> 01:22:35.283
A comedian
with serious fucking money troubles!

01:22:36.117 --> 01:22:38.828
Look, do I feel bad that I left you?

01:22:38.912 --> 01:22:41.289
Sure.
Likewise, I feel bad for your friend.

01:22:41.790 --> 01:22:42.790
But...

01:22:43.833 --> 01:22:45.669
But too fucking bad!

01:22:46.169 --> 01:22:50.882
I got two mortgages I can't afford,
I got two ex-wives,

01:22:50.966 --> 01:22:55.220
who are fucking serious
bloodsucking vampires

01:22:55.428 --> 01:22:57.889
and a kid who's in rehab
for the second time.

01:22:58.098 --> 01:23:02.143
I get on Colbert and my quote skyrockets.

01:23:02.811 --> 01:23:05.480
My profile rises.

01:23:05.855 --> 01:23:07.107
The offers come in.

01:23:07.691 --> 01:23:09.484
I'm making money again.

01:23:10.110 --> 01:23:12.988
I'm sorry your friend's gonna die,
but he had his shot.

01:23:13.446 --> 01:23:17.117
I need this, Al,
because my life depends on it.

01:23:17.325 --> 01:23:19.327
[car horns honk]

01:23:21.913 --> 01:23:22.913
What do you want?

01:23:24.040 --> 01:23:25.291
Huh?

01:23:25.917 --> 01:23:27.711
How much do you want for your slot?

01:23:29.754 --> 01:23:31.047
Are you bribing me?

01:23:32.048 --> 01:23:33.508
I call it a <i>soborno.</i>

01:23:34.801 --> 01:23:38.096
So, tell me... how much do you need?

01:23:41.933 --> 01:23:43.309
I think you should go.

01:23:55.530 --> 01:24:00.702
The first comic I ever booked
got paid 50 bucks.

01:24:01.619 --> 01:24:03.288
My take was $5.

01:24:04.122 --> 01:24:06.124
That was in 1963.

01:24:07.333 --> 01:24:14.007
And that $5 is still sitting at the bottom
of a big, fat, useless bank account

01:24:14.090 --> 01:24:18.928
with a million more fives
that never bought me a scrap of joy

01:24:19.262 --> 01:24:20.847
without the ability to earn it.

01:24:22.432 --> 01:24:26.352
You see, I'm one of those guys
who didn't work to live.

01:24:26.436 --> 01:24:27.896
I live to work.

01:24:29.105 --> 01:24:30.105
I live to work.

01:24:31.399 --> 01:24:32.525
[sighs] But now...

01:24:32.942 --> 01:24:34.235
Now, I don't work.

01:24:35.153 --> 01:24:37.489
Which means I have
to figure out how to live.

01:24:39.991 --> 01:24:43.286
So, I don't have
a fucking life right now, Max.

01:24:43.953 --> 01:24:45.121
But I need one.

01:24:46.289 --> 01:24:47.874
And you're gonna give it to me.

01:24:49.584 --> 01:24:51.044
So, I'll ask one more time.

01:24:52.420 --> 01:24:55.465
How much do you need
to let us have your slot?

01:24:58.885 --> 01:25:02.597
[announcer] <i> It's The Late Show
with Stephen Colbert.</i>

01:25:02.680 --> 01:25:05.141
<i>Tonight, Ryan Reynolds.</i>

01:25:05.767 --> 01:25:11.022
<i>Plus, Stephen welcomes Bernadette Peters
and comedian Max Becker.</i>

01:25:11.106 --> 01:25:16.236
<i>Live on tape from the Ed Sullivan Theater
in New York City, it's...</i>

01:25:16.611 --> 01:25:18.404
How you feeling, Mr Green?

01:25:19.405 --> 01:25:20.990
Could you turn that thing off?

01:25:32.961 --> 01:25:33.961
You're good.

01:25:47.892 --> 01:25:49.060
You look great.

01:25:49.894 --> 01:25:51.312
I look like shit.

01:25:51.646 --> 01:25:53.273
A big, steaming pile of it.

01:25:54.357 --> 01:25:57.443
- But your tuxedo...
- My tuxedo's older than me.

01:25:59.362 --> 01:26:00.738
At least you have an act.

01:26:00.822 --> 01:26:02.282
I don't have an act.

01:26:02.615 --> 01:26:04.534
Yeah, you don't.
That's 'cause you're senile.

01:26:04.659 --> 01:26:06.661
[Ryan] <i>This man right here is a liar.</i>

01:26:06.744 --> 01:26:08.163
[Stephen] <i>Ryan Reynolds, everybody.</i>

01:26:08.371 --> 01:26:10.373
[audience cheers]

01:26:24.721 --> 01:26:26.389
You did this, Al.

01:26:27.098 --> 01:26:28.099
Nah.

01:26:28.975 --> 01:26:29.976
It was all Max.

01:26:33.980 --> 01:26:34.980
Remember this?

01:26:37.233 --> 01:26:39.068
- Yeah.
- Go get 'em!

01:26:39.777 --> 01:26:41.779
[audience cheers]

01:26:43.239 --> 01:26:44.324
[Ryan] <i>It's Tuesday.</i>

01:26:44.824 --> 01:26:45.867
[Stephen] <i> It's Thursday!</i>

01:26:46.659 --> 01:26:48.077
<i>How dare you, Ryan!</i>

01:26:48.161 --> 01:26:49.454
Hey, Buddy!

01:26:50.622 --> 01:26:51.623
Knock 'em dead!

01:26:56.002 --> 01:26:57.002
Hey...

01:26:57.754 --> 01:26:59.172
what happened to your shoes?

01:26:59.881 --> 01:27:00.881
Long story.

01:27:01.507 --> 01:27:02.967
[Stephen] <i>Ryan Reynolds, everybody!</i>

01:27:03.218 --> 01:27:05.220
[audience cheers]

01:27:10.642 --> 01:27:12.644
<i>This a crazy story, folks.</i>

01:27:12.936 --> 01:27:17.774
<i>Fifty years ago, a comic was given a shot
on The Ed Sullivan Show</i>

01:27:17.857 --> 01:27:22.028
<i>in this very theater, but for some reason,
it never happened.</i>

01:27:23.404 --> 01:27:27.200
When I heard that he wanted to come back

01:27:27.325 --> 01:27:31.079
and give it a go again
after all that time,

01:27:31.537 --> 01:27:33.623
I was so moved

01:27:34.165 --> 01:27:38.753
that I felt
that I had to help make this happen.

01:27:39.337 --> 01:27:41.172
And so, ladies and gentlemen,

01:27:41.381 --> 01:27:45.593
welcome to the stage,
the great Buddy Green!

01:27:45.885 --> 01:27:47.887
[audience cheers]

01:27:52.517 --> 01:27:54.519
[trumpets play]

01:28:10.243 --> 01:28:11.703
[audience member whistles]

01:28:19.627 --> 01:28:20.878
[Buddy] Thank you.

01:28:21.504 --> 01:28:22.755
Thank you.

01:28:23.881 --> 01:28:25.341
You're very kind.

01:28:25.425 --> 01:28:28.011
<i>I want you to know
this is my first comeback</i>

01:28:28.094 --> 01:28:29.887
<i>without someone yelling, "Clear!"</i>

01:28:35.560 --> 01:28:37.812
<i>I've been performing
for the last couple of weeks,</i>

01:28:37.895 --> 01:28:41.816
<i>you know, cutting my teeth
in clubs all across the country</i>

01:28:42.483 --> 01:28:44.110
and I did a little TV, too.

01:28:44.193 --> 01:28:46.612
You may recognize me
from <i>America's Got Dentures.</i>

01:28:49.615 --> 01:28:50.742
See, that's a cheap joke.

01:28:50.825 --> 01:28:53.578
I used to tell a lot of cheap jokes,
but I am done.

01:28:54.287 --> 01:28:55.872
I'm done with cheap jokes.

01:28:55.955 --> 01:28:59.083
Jokes are easy. People email jokes

01:28:59.208 --> 01:29:02.879
and if you have a relative of my age,
you know exactly what I'm talking about

01:29:02.962 --> 01:29:07.967
because there is nothing more dangerous
than an old man attached to the internet.

01:29:09.469 --> 01:29:15.933
We know just enough to type
the word "funny" with one finger...

01:29:16.017 --> 01:29:18.561
My manager wouldn't have done this for me.

01:29:19.812 --> 01:29:21.939
I'm not taking any new clients right now.

01:29:26.152 --> 01:29:27.862
[Buddy] My idea of a remote control

01:29:27.945 --> 01:29:30.156
is telling my grandson
to change the channel.

01:29:30.281 --> 01:29:32.283
[audience laughs]

01:29:32.492 --> 01:29:34.660
And I don't like making fun of old people.

01:29:34.827 --> 01:29:37.205
<i>Growing old is serious business.</i>

01:29:37.288 --> 01:29:38.581
[audience laughs]

01:29:38.748 --> 01:29:41.084
<i>That's why we're angry all the time.</i>

01:29:41.376 --> 01:29:45.838
<i>And what we're really angry at is time
and you can't get angry at time,</i>

01:29:46.089 --> 01:29:50.385
<i>so we take it out on waiters and children
and people who love us.</i>

01:29:50.760 --> 01:29:55.306
Did you ever see an old person
in a restaurant not send the meal back?

01:29:56.557 --> 01:30:00.144
"Give me a perfect frigging meal.
I am about to die."

01:30:02.230 --> 01:30:04.399
<i>So, that's why I don't tell jokes anymore.</i>

01:30:05.566 --> 01:30:06.901
<i>It's a waste of time.</i>

01:30:08.194 --> 01:30:10.613
<i>Life is a big enough joke.</i>

01:30:33.761 --> 01:30:35.930
<i>And that's why we need funny people.</i>

01:30:36.722 --> 01:30:40.643
Not just on TV, but at work, at home...

01:30:41.644 --> 01:30:43.020
at the doctor's office.

01:30:44.272 --> 01:30:49.735
It took me 50 years to figure that out
and I still can't use the remote.

01:30:50.194 --> 01:30:54.490
One more thing.
Ed Sullivan - if you're watching,

01:30:54.574 --> 01:30:55.950
I'm sorry I'm late.

01:30:56.284 --> 01:30:57.285
I'll see you soon.

01:31:41.162 --> 01:31:44.999
[Sunshine] <i>Gentlemen, I am well aware
of the unpleasant news</i>

01:31:45.082 --> 01:31:46.584
<i>that I've brought you in the past.</i>

01:31:46.751 --> 01:31:50.213
<i>But I tell you something.
Nothing - and I mean nothing -</i>

01:31:50.296 --> 01:31:51.631
<i>could prepare me for this one.</i>

01:31:51.714 --> 01:31:54.884
Did you hear about Al?

01:31:56.052 --> 01:31:59.305
<i>Apparently, he lost everything.</i>

01:32:00.097 --> 01:32:02.850
<i>Forced to move into
some old folks' home in the Midwest.</i>

01:32:03.893 --> 01:32:07.355
<i>Can you imagine being sent
to a place like that?</i>

01:32:12.568 --> 01:32:13.903
<i>If I could stand up,</i>

01:32:14.445 --> 01:32:16.030
I'd hang myself.
